0:00 WHAT IS GPTBot?
3:10 What can we expect from GPT-5
5:09 When will GPT-5 be released?

OpenAI has introduced a new tool named GPTBot, marking a significant milestone in the effort to develop artificial intelligence. GPTBot is an automated web data collector with the ability to navigate the entire internet and gather text from web pages. The vast amount of textual data that GPTBot can accumulate will provide a valuable resource for training OpenAI's upcoming language models. Specifically, GPTBot is designed to support GPT-5, the next iteration of the renowned language model after GPT-4. With GPT-5, OpenAI aims to achieve a breakthrough in the development of Artificial General Intelligence (AGI). Upon success, GPT-5 will be the first AI model capable of thinking, reasoning, and problem-solving at a human-like level. This will unlock new applications and possibilities for AI that we have never seen before.

In reality, the reason behind ChatGPT's ability to generate such great content lies in the massive amount of text data collected from the internet, all thanks to GPTBot. It's like an enormous information library that the models use to understand and respond to your requests. And if you're curious about how GPTBot selects which websites to explore and which ones to avoid, GPTBot follows specific rules and principles to ensure the collected data is of high quality and respects both privacy rights and the rights of individuals. To illustrate, GPTBot exclusively explores websites that anyone can access without needing to go through paywalls or log in with usernames and passwords. It deliberately avoids collecting data from websites containing Personally Identifiable Information (PII), such as names, addresses, phone numbers, or email addresses of individuals. Moreover, it filters out content that violates OpenAI's policies, such as content containing provocative, violent, or explicit language. But what if you're a website owner and you don't want GPTBot to gather data from your website? You have the option to do that. You can insert a specific line into your website's robots.txt file to instruct the information-gathering process to stay away from your website. This requires GPTBot not to crawl any pages on your website. Now, GPT-5 is the next major language model expected from OpenAI, following the previous releases of GPT-3.5 and GPT-4. Although there's still very little information about it, there are some clues indicating that OpenAI is working on it and has plans to release it soon. For instance, OpenAI filed a trademark application for "GPT-5" with the United States Patent and Trademark Office (USPTO) in July 2023. This application covers various types of software related to language models and AI. The application is currently pending examination by the USPTO.

But what can we expect from GPT-5 in terms of capabilities and features? Well, based on previous versions of the GPT model, we can assume GPT-5 will be a major upgrade over GPT-4 in size, accuracy, and flexibility. For example:

In terms of size, GPT-4 comprised 175 billion parameters. This was already hugely significant when comparing it to most other existing language models. Now, GPT-5 is predicted to have an even larger number of parameters, potentially in the trillions. What does this mean for us? Basically, GPT-5 will be able to store more information and have a larger memory capacity than any human, making it an extremely powerful tool. When it comes to accuracy, GPT-4 demonstrated superior performance on various natural language processing (NLP) tasks and benchmarks. These include areas like natural language understanding (NLU), natural language generation (NLG), question answering (QA), etc. However, GPT-5 is expected to surpass these achievements even further. It may reach new heights in accuracy and fluency, generating text and speech that is more human-like in communication.
